    switch (value % 10) {
        case 1:
            return value + "st";
        case 2:
            return value + "nd";
        case 3:
            return value + "rd";
        default:
            return value + "th";
    }
}
```

This function works for all positive integers. However, it doesn't handle edge cases like 0 or negative numbers, or non-integer numbers. Also, it doesn't check if the input is a number.

